The Saltbound Custodians are undead embalmers, acolytes, and legal-priests in Khardaan who
continue attempting to execute Perpetual Custody exactly as written in the necropolis's
operational mandate. They are the orderly face of Khardaan's undead factions—hostile to looters
and improvisers, but not hostile to living pilgrims who engage with appropriate procedural
respect. Their function was the preservation and administration of the salt-law stores, oath
records, and scarcity governance infrastructure that underpinned Khardaan's mortuary economy.
The Perpetual Custody mandate required that natron supplies, sacred salts, and the water-debt
ledgers governing burial water quotas be maintained indefinitely under custodial authority.
The Custodians were originally a living body—professional embalmers and legal-priests who
managed the natron extraction and processing operations that supplied all burial operations in
the region. When Khardaan's governance collapsed, the Custodians were included in an emergency
binding protocol that converted them to undead form to ensure Perpetual Custody could outlast
the crisis that was destroying the necropolis's living administration. They have now been
executing that mandate without interruption or review for longer than the mandate's original
institutional context survived.

