The Neon Covenant's institutional design specifically prohibits permanent emergency designations precisely because the Custodian case illustrates the failure mode: the emergency measure becomes the institution, continuing in emergency mode indefinitely.
The Jade Magistracy's notes on the Custodian case are referenced alongside the Binder Collegium analysis — both are examples of administrative bodies that outlasted their governance context.
