flags RAKUEN KETHARI
---
Kethari water-memory intersects with the Saltbound Custodians through natron extraction and its relationship to regional aquifer behavior.
Khardaan's natron deposits were managed under the Perpetual Custody mandate using calibrated extraction rates designed to prevent depletion.
Kethari communities preserved observations of aquifer behavior before, during, and after Khardaan's governance collapse, including how managed extraction compared to the unmanaged extraction that followed.
The Custodians' extraction rate was significantly lower than what the aquifer could sustain — conservative management for the long term. The post-collapse unmanaged period caused measurable aquifer depletion.
The Custodians' restored management has partially reversed this; Kethari water-memory records show aquifer recovery consistent with the Custodians' calibrated approach.
Kethari do not evaluate the Custodians institutionally — they evaluate them as functional water managers, which is a different and more favorable assessment.

